$ABCDE$ is a regular pentagon.  $AP$, $AQ$ and $AR$ are the perpendiculars dropped from $A$ onto $CD$, $CB$ extended and $DE$ extended, respectively.  Let $O$ be the center of the pentagon.  If $OP = 1$, then find $AO + AQ + AR$.

[asy]

